Package: BioHEARTResilience
Type: Package
Title: Identify Cardiovascular Disease Resilience Phenotypes Using CACS Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Matthew", "Shu", , "matthew.shu@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "YOUR-ORCID-ID"))
Description: Implements a novel methodology to classify resilient and susceptible 
    phenotypes to coronary artery disease by comparing observed coronary artery 
    calcium scores (CACS) against expected values derived from ensemble 
    cardiovascular risk scoring. The package integrates multiple validated risk 
    scores (FRS, ASCVD, MESA, SCORE2) and uses zero-inflated negative binomial 
    regression to calculate risk-adjusted CACS percentiles.
